ipxe: ipxe (open source network boot firmware)
ipxe:
ipxe: iPXE is the leading open source network boot firmware. It provides a
ipxe: full PXE implementation enhanced with additional features such as 
ipxe: booting from a web server via HTTP or HTTPS, booting from an iSCSI,
ipxe: FCoE, or AoE SAN, controlling the boot process with a script, and
ipxe: creating interactive forms and menus.
ipxe:
ipxe: You can use iPXE to replace the existing PXE ROM on your network 
ipxe: card, or you can chainload into iPXE to obtain the features of iPXE
ipxe: without the hassle of reflashing.
